===== Program =====

It is important to have installed beforehand in your laptops the VO-tools to be used in the School, namely:

     * [[http://aladin.u-strasbg.fr/java/download/Aladin.jar|ALADIN]] (Download the Aladin.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -Xmx2048m -jar Aladin.jar**"). Official version: v9.033b 
     * [[http://aladin.u-strasbg.fr/java/AladinV10.jar|ALADINV10]] (Download the Aladinv10.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -Xmx2048m -jar Aladinv10.jar**"). Aladin V10 Avant Premiere 
     * [[http://www.star.bris.ac.uk/~mbt/topcat/topcat-full.jar|TOPCAT]] (Download the topcat-full.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -jar topcat-full.jar**"). Official version: v4.5
     * [[http://svo2.cab.inta-csic.es/theory/vosa/|VOSA]] (Web server. You don't need to install anything). Official version: v5.1
     * [[http://www.star.bris.ac.uk/~mbt/stilts/stilts.jar|STILTS]] (Download the stilts.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -jar stilts.jar**"). Official version: v3.2-1 
     * [[http://star-www.dur.ac.uk/~pdraper/splat/splat-vo/splat-vo.jar| SPLAT-VO]] (Download the splat-vo.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -jar splat-vo.jar**"). Official version: 3.11. Note that, unlike ALADIN, TOPCAT or STILTS, the //splat-vo.jar// file does not launch the tool but an installation program. Once the installation has been completed, you should launch the tool with a command like this:
        * **$XXXX/splat-vo/bin/splat/splat&**

